ExecDesc.value: Microsoft Windows Fax Services Cover Page Editor Heap Buffer Overflow

EngDesc.value: A heap buffer overflow vulnerability exists in Microsoft Windows Fax Services. The vulnerability is due to insufficient validation of a drawing object data while parsing Microsoft Fax cover page files. Remote attackers could exploit this vulnerability by enticing the target user to open a specially crafted Fax cover page file.Successful exploitation could result in execution of arbitrary code within the security context of the currently logged in user. An unsuccessful attempt will terminate the affected application abnormally.
